<p>If the scratching posts above don’t seem like the perfect fit for your cat, you’ll be glad to know we have a few more options for you. Here are five more unique cat scratching posts you might like.</p>
<div class="su-row card-review">
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><span class="product-review-heading">#6 </span>Best Horizontal Scratching Post: <a href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:best-cat-scratching-post/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fsmartcat-bootsies-combination%2Fdp%2F49129" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener">SmartCat Bootsie’s Combination Scratcher</a></h2>
<p><img decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-26784 aligncenter" src="https://allaboutcats.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/SmartCat-Bootsies-Three-in-One-Cat-Scratcher.png" alt="" width="350" height="190" /></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="amz" href="https://prf.hn/click/camref:1101l4atA/pubref:best-cat-scratching-post/destination:https%3A%2F%2Fwww.chewy.com%2Fsmartcat-bootsies-combination%2Fdp%2F49129" target="_blank" rel="sponsored noopener noreferrer">View On Chewy</a></p>
<p>If you have a cat who enjoys horizontal scratching, this combination scratcher may be a good choice. It measures 24 inches long by 7 inches wide and can be used vertically or horizontally. You can even mount it to the wall or hang it over a door.</p>
<p>This combination cat scratcher is made from heavy-duty materials to give your cat years of use. It’s made from durable sisal material that naturally encourages scratching and features rubber feet to keep it from sliding on the floor.</p>
<h3>Pros:</h3>
<ul class="pro">
<li>Allows for vertical or horizontal scratching</li>
<li>Heavy-duty construction with durable sisal material</li>
<li>Affordably priced under $25</li>
